description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you in your Final year of your Nursing Degree?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;vibrant and stimulating career opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Then working nursing at ULHT is for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ULHT is a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;patient-centred organisation whose vision and values include safety, excellence, compassion and respect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit newly qualified nurses wishing to start their registered nursing journey with us in Autumn 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have sites across Lincolnshire: Lincoln, Boston, Grantham and Louth, which all have new and exciting opportunities within a variety of specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no need to decide which area you wish to work in at this stage – all that is needed right now is for us to get the recruitment ball rolling! You will be asked to make a preference request at a later date. We listened to feedback from our previous Newly Qualified Nurses who joined our Organisation; they suggested that more time was needed to make the right decision. We will work together to find the right post for you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are excited about the opportunities that the new Lincoln Medical school will bring to our organisation. Creating an inclusive and caring environment for our staff and patients, providing a vehicle for growth to develop the next generation of healthcare providers and leaders. And as a trust we are working collaboratively with the University to make the most of these opportunities and further develop a culture of excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to COVID, the Interview stage will be managed in an alternative way, details will follow your application after the shortlisting stage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Kerrie Linger&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Matron for Workforce and Clinical Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Kerrie.Linger@ULH.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
